def: The sacred baboon of Egypt (Cynocephalus Hamadryas).
To flower, or cause to flower, again. Sylvester.
Having the stigma visible at the throad of a gamopetalouscorolla, while the stamens are concealed in the tube; -- said ofdimorphous flowers. The opposite of Ant: thrum-eyed.
A preparation of antimony with which Mohammedan men anointtheir eyelids.
To be convereted into a powder or friable substance, or into acalx, by the action of heat. "Calcining without fusion" Newton.
A college servant; -- so called in Cambridge, England; atOxford called a scout. [Cant]
Any cephalopod having a siphonate shell.

Liquefaction; the act of causing (something) to melt, or theprocess of becoming melted.
